Residents have appealed to the Samburu County government to construct public toilets in three sub county headquarters. They said visitors of Wamba town in Samburu East are forced to answer their call of nature near sources of water which poses a health risk. ALSO READ:

The everlasting love story is brewed in Samburu Patrick Lembwakita, a resident of Wamba town said:"There are no public toilets, people help themselves in nearby rivers and in wells." Speaking yesterday in Maralal, county Finance executive Jonathan Leisen said the county will construct toilets.